TECprogress

Fabian Blombach

18/10/2019

This script describes the generation of generalised linear models for the progression of TEC-Spt4/5 to TEC-Spt4/5-Elf1 during exponential growth. Negative binomial models were used to model count data that showed overdispersion. Raw coverage of Elf1 in the promoter region was modelled. The normalisation against the chromatin input was built into the model by including an offest term with raw chromatin input coverage.

export PATH=$PATH:/Users/fabianblombach/miniconda3/bin
if [ -d temp ]; then rm -Rf temp; fi
mkdir temp
bedtools slop -i $TSS -g  ../Genomes/Sso_NCBI/SsoP2.sizes -s -l 7 -r 4 > temp/slop.bed

bedtools getfasta -name -s -bed temp/slop.bed -fi ../Genomes/Sso_NCBI/NC_002754.fna -fo temp/DNA.fasta
#Temperature in Kelvin
temp=349.15
#Salt concentration in molar
salt= 0.025

#load reference values from SantaLucia Jr paper (PNAS 1998)
NN<-read.table("~/HTS/scripts/NN_thermodynamics.txt", header=T, sep="\t")
NN$ΔH<-as.numeric(as.character(NN$ΔH))
NN$ΔS<-as.numeric(as.character(NN$ΔS))
#delH is in kcal/mol, while delS is in cal/mol*k, calculate the delG in kcal/mol
NN$ΔG <- NN$ΔH - (NN$ΔS*temp/1000)

#load alignment of promoter sequences (output from bedtools getfasta -tab)
require(seqinr)
input<-read.fasta("temp/DNA.fasta", forceDNAtolower=T)
mono<-as.data.frame(matrix(unlist(input), nrow=length(input), byrow=T), row.names=names(input))
row.names(mono)<-gsub('(+)',"",row.names(mono), fixed=T)
row.names(mono)<-gsub('(-)',"",row.names(mono), fixed=T)
# loop to make table with dinucleotides
dinuc<-matrix(rep("N", times=nrow(mono)*(ncol(mono)-1)), nrow=nrow(mono))
for (j in 1:nrow(mono)) {
  for (i in 1:(ncol(mono)-1)) { 
  dinuc[j,i] <- paste0(mono[j,i], mono[j,i+1]) 
  } 
}
# replace dinucleotides with corresponding deltaG values
dinucG<-dinuc
for (k in 1:16) {
dinucG[dinucG == NN[k,1]]<- NN[k,4]
}
dinucG<-data.frame(matrix(as.numeric(dinucG), ncol=ncol(dinuc)))


# replace monocleotides with corresponding deltaG values for terminal nucleotides
monoG<-as.matrix(mono, nrow=nrow(mono))
for (k in 17:20) {
  monoG[monoG == NN[k,1]]<- NN[k,4]
}
monoG<-data.frame(matrix(as.numeric(monoG), ncol=ncol(monoG)))

calculate Spt45Bd and input occupancy for linear modelling

rm temp/trashme.npz;
head -n 2 temp/trashme.tab > temp/Coverage.tab;

read matrix file and split based on samples

cov <- read.table(paste0("temp/Coverage.tab"), sep="\t", header=F)

Calculate deltaG for -5 ot +7 window by summing up dinucleotide G values

Automatic model selection with step() function including binary interaction terms, minimizing BIC

#function to calculate BIC
bic<-function(model) {-model$twologlik  + (length(model$coefficients)+1) * log(nrow(model$model))}


model.null<- suppressWarnings(glm.nb(Elf1_r1_promCov ~ offset(log(Inp1_promCov)), data=data.Merged2))
#full model including all binary interaction terms
model.bin <- suppressWarnings(glm.nb(Elf1_r1_promCov ~ offset(log(Inp1_promCov)) + log(spt45_r1_promoter) + deltaG + log(TFB1_foldR1) + log(TFEb_foldR1) + log(cpsf1_r1_promoter) + I(log(spt45_r1_promoter)*deltaG) + I(log(spt45_r1_promoter)*log(TFB1_foldR1)) + I(log(spt45_r1_promoter)*log(TFEb_foldR1)) + I(log(spt45_r1_promoter)*log(cpsf1_r1_promoter)) + I(deltaG*log(TFB1_foldR1)) + I(deltaG*log(TFEb_foldR1)) + I(deltaG*log(cpsf1_r1_promoter)) + I(log(TFB1_foldR1)*log(TFEb_foldR1)) + I(log(TFB1_foldR1)*log(cpsf1_r1_promoter)) + I(log(TFEb_foldR1)*log(cpsf1_r1_promoter)), data=data.Merged2))

model.step<-step(object=model.null, scope=list(upper=model.bin$call, lower=model.null$call), data=data.Merged2, trace=F, k = log(nrow(data.Merged2)), direction = "forward")
bic(model.step)
